let a = [1];
for (let i=0;i<2;i++) {
    console.log(a[i]);
}

The error that this code throws is "TypeError: Cannot read property '1' of undefined." 

This error occurs because the variable "a" is an array with only one element, but the for loop is iterating over two indices. On the second iteration of the loop, "a[1]" is undefined and cannot be logged to the console. 

To fix this error, adjust the for loop to only run for the length of the array "a":

```
let a = [1];
for (let i=0; i<a.length; i++) {
  console.log(a[i]);
}
```

This code will iterate over array "a" only once, print out the value "1", and then stop.
